  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Revier Mountain Lodge is on a bed and breakfast basis.</p>
<p>Each morning you can enjoy a varied buffet breakfast with a range of sweet and savoury options including croissants, breads, jams, cold meats and regional cheeses, cornflakes, museli, seeds and fruits. Gluten free bread, soy milk and lactose free milks are available on request - please advise us of any special dietary requirements at the time of booking.</p>
<p>Dinner is not included; however tasty bar food is available from the Fox House Bar. Alternatively, the restaurants in the centre of Saas Fee are just a short walk away.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>Brand new for winter 24/25, the Revier Mountain Lodge is a modern cabin style hotel with a fantastic location in <a data-udi="umb://document/f1003f9fd15e4187b02398fa5c12dc50" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f1003f9fd15e4187b02398fa5c12dc50}" title="Saas Fee">Saas Fee</a>. The Revier Mountain lodge is Green Key accredited and has been awarded the level three Swisstainable certification, demonstrating their commitment to environmental preservation and highlighting its dedication to sustainable development. </p>
<h2>Modern hotel</h2>
<p>If you are looking for a modern and comfortable place to stay during your ski holiday in <a data-udi="umb://document/52fab17731fa49639f8a0841e064a064" href="/{localLink:umb://document/52fab17731fa49639f8a0841e064a064}" title="Switzerland">Switzerland</a>, the Revier Mountain Lodge is an excellent choice. Recently built the lodge offers compact cabin style accommodation in the centre of Saas Fee. The cabin style rooms include lots of wood and large panoramic windows with a fantastic view of the mountains and resort. The hotel has a spacious restaurant and bar area, including a concert stage and a cozy lounge with a fireplace, so it's a great spot to socialise after a day on the slopes.</p>
<h2>Bed &amp; Breakfast</h2>
<p>Available on Bed and Breakfast, you can enjoy a tasty buffet breakfast with a classic continental offering before heading out onto the slopes. The evening is yours to do as you please, we recommend heading to the Fox House bar for a drink - There's over 30 unique beers available, and a wide selection of gins to choose from. There is often live music or DJ set on the weekends, you can even perform in front of the audience. The resort centre is also snowballs throw away where you can find a variety of restaurants serving delicious Swiss specialties, and international favourites.</p>
<p><strong>Exclusive to Inghams</strong></p>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with the Revier Mountain Lodge, we are the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>]]></description>
